claim: Cell- and egg-based flu vaccines have the potential to develop mutations during production, which may reduce their effectiveness.
explanation: A screenshot of the front matter and table of contents of an MMWR report, showing section headings and page numbers (e.g., Introduction; Methods; Summary Changes and Updates; Recommendations for Use of Influenza Vaccines; Influenza Vaccine Composition and Available Vaccines; Storage and Handling of Influenza Vaccines; Additional Sources of Information; References) and an editorial staff listing. The image contains only the table of contents and publication details without any discussion of vaccine production methods, mutations, or their impact on effectiveness, so it does not support the claim. Note: None
